This article is a presidential proclamation by Barack Obama commemorating the 50th anniversary of the Office of the United States Trade Representative (USTR). The USTR was established in 1962 with the goal of promoting and securing trade agreements with partner countries. The proclamation highlights the agency's role in advancing trade policy, opening new markets for American exports, and creating jobs. It also mentions USTR's efforts to level the playing field for American workers and promote stability, transparency, and accountability in international trade. The proclamation recognizes the professionals who have upheld USTR's mission and calls upon all Americans to observe the anniversary with appropriate programs and activities.